#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.217"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.217:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.217:0.2"
msgid "22. Akkosakavagga"
msgstr "22. Abuse"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.217:0.3"
msgid "217. Paṭhamaapāsādikasutta"
msgstr "217. Uninspiring Conduct (1st)"

# This should be interpreted following AN 4.103 etc.
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.217:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā apāsādike."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of uninspiring conduct."

msgctxt "an5.217:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.217:1.3"
msgid "Attāpi attānaṃ upavadati, "
msgstr "You blame yourself. "

msgctxt "an5.217:1.4"
msgid "anuvicca viññū garahanti, "
msgstr "After examination, sensible people criticize you. "

msgctxt "an5.217:1.5"
msgid "pāpako kittisaddo abbhuggacchati, "
msgstr "You get a bad reputation. "

msgctxt "an5.217:1.6"
msgid "sammūḷho kālaṃ karoti, "
msgstr "You feel lost when you die. "

msgctxt "an5.217:1.7"
msgid ""
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"And when your body breaks up, after death, you’re reborn in a place of loss, "
"a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "an5.217:1.8"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā apāsādike."
msgstr "These are the five drawbacks of uninspiring conduct."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.217:2.1"
msgid "Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā pāsādike."
msgstr "There are these five benefits of inspiring conduct."

msgctxt "an5.217:2.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.217:2.3"
msgid "Attāpi attānaṃ na upavadati, "
msgstr "You don’t blame yourself. "

msgctxt "an5.217:2.4"
msgid "anuvicca viññū pasaṃsanti, "
msgstr "After examination, sensible people praise you. "

msgctxt "an5.217:2.5"
msgid "kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggacchati, "
msgstr "You get a good reputation. "

msgctxt "an5.217:2.6"
msgid "asammūḷho kālaṃ karoti, "
msgstr "You don’t feel lost when you die. "

msgctxt "an5.217:2.7"
msgid "kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"And when the body breaks up, after death, you’re reborn in a good place, a "
"heavenly realm."

msgctxt "an5.217:2.8"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā pāsādike”ti."
msgstr "These are the five benefits of inspiring conduct.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.217:2.9"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
